Reasoning: The paper discusses embedding learning, which is a subfield of machine learning and falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses mapping embedding models to cognitive memory functions, which falls under the category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also discusses query answering, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence and falls under the category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses latent variable models, which is a subfield of neural networks and falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper discusses the technical aspects of modelling temporal knowledge graphs, which falls under the category of cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
